Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{24%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve and peel @red onion{1}. Thinly slice one half; grate remaining half until you have 2 TBSP (save the rest for another use). Zest ½ tsp zest from @lime{2}, then cut each into quarters. Thinly slice @Roma Tomato{2}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, half the @fry seasoning{2%tablespoon}, and a few big pinches of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast in oven until browned and tender, about ~{25%minutes}, tossing halfway through.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, toss together sliced onion, juice from all but one lime quarter, ¼ tsp @sugar{3/4%teaspoon}, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Set aside to pickle, tossing occasionally. In another small bowl, stir together @sour cream{8%tablespoon}, lime zest, ½ tsp sugar, juice from remaining lime quarter, and 1 tsp water. Add @sriracha{2%teaspoon} to taste. Season with salt.

In a #large bowl{}, mix @ground beef{20%ounce}, grated onion, and remaining Fry Seasoning. Using your hands, gently shape mixture into four evenly sized patties, each slightly wider than the @potato buns{4}. Season with plenty of salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat (we used nonstick). Add patties and cook ~{4%minutes} on one side, then flip and top with @Cheddar Cheese{4%slices}. Cook until browned on second side and desired doneness is reached, ~{3-5%minutes} more.

Drain liquid from pickled onion. Halve buns. Spread as much crema as you like onto bottom halves. Fill buns with patties, tomatoes, and onion. Divide burgers and potatoes between plates. Serve with any remaining crema for dipping.

> TIP: Toast buns if desired.